  "text": "The CSS style change propagation through Chromium's Blink rendering pipeline follows these key stages:\n\n1. **Style Resolution** (third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h): The StyleResolver class (line 63) is responsible for resolving computed styles for DOM elements based on the document's collection of stylesheets. It takes CSS rules and applies them to elements to produce ComputedStyle objects.\n\n2. **Layout Tree Construction** (third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h): The LayoutObject class (line 270) is the base class for the layout tree. When styles are resolved, they trigger the creation and update of LayoutObject instances, which represent the layout tree structure. Each LayoutObject corresponds to a DOM element and contains layout information.\n\n3. **Painting Layer Abstraction** (third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h): The PaintLayer class (line 174) represents the painting layer abstraction. It handles complex painting operations like opacity, clipping, and filters. PaintLayers are created for certain LayoutObjects that need special painting treatment and compose the painting tree used during the paint phase.\n\n4. **Paint Controller & Display Items** (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h and third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h): The PaintController class (line 131) is responsible for processing display items as they are produced and creating a final paint artifact. The DisplayItemList class (line 28) is a container for the list of display items of various types that record the paint operations. These classes implement the display list mechanism that records all paint operations for later replay to the graphics layer.\n\nThe pipeline flows: CSS Style Changes → StyleResolver (computes styles) → Layout Engine updates LayoutObjects → PaintLayers organize the tree → PaintController records operations → DisplayItemList stores paint commands."
}

